The President's remarks on the occasion of Rosh Hashanah focus on extending warm wishes for the new year to members of the Jewish faith. He emphasizes the importance of reflection and repentance during this time and highlights the opportunity for renewal and reconciliation for individuals, families, communities, and nations. The President calls for empathy, rejecting prejudice and intolerance, and standing up against anti-Semitism. He also expresses the desire for lasting peace and security for Israel, mentioning his administration's efforts in pursuing this goal. The President acknowledges the resilience and commitment of the Jewish people and their role as a "light unto the nations." He concludes by wishing a healthy, peaceful, and sweet new year to all who celebrate Rosh Hashanah.